            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "The request data is the unparsed, undecoded bytes that came as request body. If you want unicode you can decode it yourself:\n\n```\nrequest_text = request.data.decode('utf-8')\n```\n\nAnd if you happen to need the parsed JSON content, flask provides a convenience attribute, `request.json`. See [the documentation on request data](http://flask.pocoo.org/docs/api/#incoming-request-data) for more information.\n"
